CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT * FROM Crop</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select * from weathersensor</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select system_type, capacity from irrigationsystem</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.field_name from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.field_name from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id</s>

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, h.health_status FROM Crop c JOIN CropHealth h ON c.crop_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, h.health_status from crop c join crophealth h on c.crop_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_type, f.area from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id</s>

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_type, f.area FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id</s>

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_type, f.area from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM WeatherSensor w JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON w.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON i.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp from weathersensor w join irrigationsystem i on w.field_id = i.field_id join crophealth h on i.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM WeatherSensor w JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON w.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON i.field_id = h.field_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id</s>

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

<t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>select c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp from crop c join field f on c.crop_id = f.crop_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id join weathersensor w on f.field_id = w.field_id join irrigationsystem i on f.field_id = i.field_id join crophealth h on f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><s>SELECT c.crop_name, f.area, h.health_status, w.location, i.system_type, h.timestamp FROM Crop c JOIN Field f ON c.crop_id = f.crop_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id JOIN WeatherSensor w ON f.field_id = w.field_id JOIN IrrigationSystem i ON f.field_id = i.field_id JOIN CropHealth h ON f.field_id = h.field_id</s>
